node.title: Live - Hutt Valley awaits latest COVID figures after case detected, locations of interest revealed
node.content: ["All eyes are on the Hutt Valley on Thursday to see if the lower North Island area has recorded any new cases of COVID-19.", "The Ministry of Health announced on Wednesday that a single case of COVID-19 had been detected there with a link to the Lakes DHB. A number of locations of interest were released for Lower and Upper Hutt, with the public told to get tested if they had any symptoms.", "11am - Kia ora, good morning and welcome to Newshub's live updates for Thursday.", "We are waiting for the 1pm Ministry of Health update which will reveal if any new cases of COVID-19 have been found in Hutt Valley.", "The area recorded a case on Wednesday, prompting a number of locations of interest to be identified in both Lower and Upper Hutt."]
